## Long-Running Operations Notification

**ONLY send SMS when operation takes more than 5 minutes from when agent started working.**

**Auto-detect SMS number:**
```powershell
$smsNumber = switch ($env:USERNAME) {
    "FKGEISTA" { "+4797188358" }
    "FKSVEERI" { "+4795762742" }
    "FKMISTA"  { "+4799348397" }
    "FKCELERI" { "+4745269945" }
    default    { "+4797188358" }
}

Send-Sms $smsNumber "<summary of what changed and short result>"
```

**SMS message format:**
- Keep under 160 characters
- Include: operation type, files affected, and status (success/failure)
- Example: `DedgeCommon v1.5.20 deployed. WorkObject pattern added. All tests passed.`

**When to send:**
- ONLY after operation completes AND elapsed time > 5 minutes
- Before final response to user
- Include error summary if operation failed

**Do NOT send SMS for:**
- Operations under 5 minutes
- Interactive operations requiring user input
- Simple read-only queries
- Quick fixes, simple builds
